From 1961b1ac7ed4eb25e3a6059c30c6f834a6751cef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luciano <luciano@caratori.com.ar>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 08:19:34 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix 35 inconsistencies and packaging issues across codebase

Critical fixes:
- setup.py: Fix nested path bug reading __init__.py version, correct repo URL,
  update python_requires to >=3.10, add package_data for assets
- Unify duplicate enums between models.py and config/taxonomy.py (Scale,
  ExtractionTier, QCStatus, DebtType now use consistent values)
- Fix Ofgem scraper casing bug: normalize registry keys to uppercase,
  add case-insensitive lookup in get_scraper()
- Fix units mismatch: models.py financial fields (kd_nominal, ke_nominal,
  wacc_nominal, etc.) now use percentage points to match thresholds.py

High-priority fixes:
- Add pyproject.toml with modern build system configuration
- Add MIT LICENSE file
- Add MANIFEST.in for source distribution
- Fix CLI/README mismatches: correct command syntax, flags, and examples
- Align dashboard port to 8765 across cli.py and server.py
- Add start_server() function to dashboard/server.py (imported by cli.py)
- Add .env.example with documented environment variables
- Add tests/ directory with initial model tests

Medium fixes:
- Remove duplicate __version__/__author__ from config/__init__.py and
  extraction/__init__.py
- Replace deprecated urllib3 method_whitelist with allowed_methods
- Use centralized USER_AGENT from config.settings in scrapers/base.py
- Add data/extracted/ and data/final/ to .gitignore
- Defer directory creation in settings.py to avoid import side effects
- Fix extraction pipeline to use ExtractionTier enum values
- Fix README: correct tier count (3 not 4), remove missing doc link

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
